okay... last night (teusday night) me and tom at about 10:30 decided to go find something to do.  we left my house in my truck and we saw some spotlights, we thought, hey, we have nothing else to do, lets find out where they're coming from.  so for about a half hour we tracked the lights on a magical quest and wound up at a goddamn meijers... well it was a brand new one out on 10 mile so we went in.  we met 3 other guys there that did the same thing that we did and all 3 live on my street. now is that odd? okay, sure, whatever, it was great.  now just about a half hour ago this guy calls me... not so wierd, but i have no clue who the guy is at first... i can tell he's a black dude and he keeps trying to get me to buy this dog from him... i tell him no, i got one, blah blah blah, and we start talkin and shit.  hes an older guy, dont know how old, but yeah... so we're all talking an shit and he like lost his job, getting evicted, car wont run and he has no money to fix it, yadda yadda, but i feel bad so i wont hang up or nothing... he gives me his phone number and tells me to call him when i get some more 400$ dro... haha but will i call him? i might actually... hahaha... his name is Mr. Schmitty and he called me (in joking form) macaroni... his name is Big Schmitty from Detroit City (but he lives in GR) and when we talked about chicks he referred to them as Chilles and said that he wanted to "pat their booboos"... if anyone has any information on a Mr. Schmitty, please inform me as soon as possible... thank you...

okay yeah, a couple days ago i was nailing some nice shit off of this 4 set, right? fs and bs 180s, huge shuvit, kickflip, fake bs 180... cool and all i guess, i had some nice high stuff.  now we go over to the next building and what do i see? its a short ass runway with a 4, another short run and a 4, and yet another short run to a final four set.  way hard too cuz you cant set up very good cuz by the time you land you're at the next fuckin set. well i do it sloppy, screw it up a few times, then i try one final time. land or no im goin home right after.  so i do the first fine, second good, and on to the third it's my best run yet.  what do i do? my front foot goes to far forward and it comes off the front and all my weight rolls and buckles my ankle under me.  i lay there and think, shit.  yeah, uh, there were actually a few people watcin i didnt know or nothin, they were just people.  lucky me i didnt feel like a dumbass trippin out on a 4 cuz one kid was on his bike and he tride to endo on the curb or some shit and he fell.  so i felt better but it was hard as shit.  you think 3 consecutive 4's, no prob right? wrong.  the short runs fucked me over big time.  at least i did it sloppy tho, thats good enough i guess. now when im all healed up im gonna go apply myself at the HS and do some shit on the 5 out there, then maybe come on back to the empty buildin by coit and hit the 6... try and pull what i was doin o the 4, seeing as how i was doin it all without too much trouble and hittin some stuff first try...

i cannot believe that somebody actually reads this... nobody ever comments... eh, well yeah i almost died this morning... almost, oh well, maybe next time.  I stayed up REALLY late till like 6 AM and went driving like a fuckhead in the pouring rain and my truck was slipping all over and i almost went off road a few times (i was heading north on old 131 - now known as the east beltline/northland drive) and i wound up in Big Rapids when the rain slowed.  I was spending my 45 minutes on the way back listening to Red Hot Chili Peppers and i was really tired and i fell asleep driving and my truck started to drift off (bad news cuz i was going 75-80 with trees all around).  I was all the way off of the road and my truck went into the grass and it was super bumpy and i woke up barely in time to throw the wheel back to the road and skid a little.... the cluster of trees that i missed was about 10 to 15 feet in front of me when i swerved... to think that i was milliseconds from dying is a great thought... oh well, maybe I'll have better luck next time, eh?  Catch you later, maybe...
